Nov 18 2009 	Budget hotel - you get what you pay for!	This hotel is in Bur Dubai which is not a tourist area. The rooms are big and although generally clean the furniture is old and there were fingerprints around the light switches. My room had a massive king size bed and two air conditioning units. There was also a sofa with coffee table and a television which lots of channels. The bathroom was big but again with old style fittings. The nightclub downstairs can be a bit noisy. This hotel is a good choice for budget travellers on short stays.	
