Sep 23 2009 	Best bet for the money	It is centrally located 10 min from the airport and Burj Tower. Rooms are very clean and big. Breakfast is good. Probably it is best bet for the money. Shops and Supermarket are just in next buildings. We had booked through GTA and it cost us AED 250 per day. They are good in arranging nice desert safari at very competitive price. Only drawback is very costly Internet and no Wi-Fi in rooms. Though they have pub at ground floor, the noise is well controlled. We did not hear any noise even in the corridor.	
Jun 5 2009 	"Very nice staff."	I stayed on two different ocassions for two nights each in May. Nice price with very helpful and courteous staff. The price is affordable and rooms are nice. The Jockey Pub was very cozy and atmospheric. Lots of working girls but I was able to comfortably drink a few beers without being harrassed any more than I wanted to be. The draft beer was poured in a bigger than normal glass and was only 14 dirhams. Security was tight as ladies were not allowed to approach you in the lobby or out front. If a lady was escorted upstairs by a guest an ID was left at the front desk. Mall was close by and Taxi's were abundent. Staff was excellent and helpful. I will definately stay only there as I go through Dubai every 3 months or so.	
