Mar 23 2009 	You get what you pay for	An interesting place. For the price paid (100Dhs for a night including room service) what more could one expect? The room was basic, but clean although the air conditioning was a bit clanky (although I didn't hear any pigeons...) but the noise from the Jockey bar downstairs was very loud. The bathroom although clean was not up to much as the hot water was either off or unavailable and there was no plug for the bath so it was a choice of shower or shower! The bed was comfortable and importantly the sheets were fresh.The Jockey Bar has, I believe, been unfairly slated in reviews on this site. Yes, there are certain ladies of ill-repute ( a varied selection at that :) ) that frequent the bar, but they will not approach you unless you make indications to them that you are &quot;looking for business&quot;. The beer is good and it is a good old fashiooned smokey pub that can be enjoyed without getting any hassle.On the whole I thoroughly enjoyed it!	
Aug 8 2008	A good budget hotel in Dubai..	I stayed seven nights at the Panorama Bur Dubai. Compared to other budget hotels either in Bur Dubai or Deira, i found this one being the nicest. The location is fine since you are close to Malls and not far from the Beach Community ( Jumeirah, Umm Suqeim ).The rooms are acceptable and the staff will clean everyday and change the towels and sheets. The room air conditioning can be noisy, however and since i always sleep with ear plugs i could sleep well. The beds are confortable.If i have an advise to give you, when booking either on the phone or through the internet, ask for a top floor room ( there is six floors in the Panorama Bur Dubai ), you will still hear the loud music from the Jockey's Club, but less than if you would stay on the first three floors ( actually i can barely imagine how people could stay a single night on the lower floors...).The staff is effective so is the room service, the food is good when you order to your room and delivered within twenty minutes. The breakfast at the restaurant downstairs is vey basic and still acceptable for the price.The Jockey's Club at the lobby entrance is a nice place for a drink, howvere be aware that it is a pick-up point which mean that there is a lot of chinese, philippinas hookers, however they will not bother you unless you ask for it....The Philippino girl at the reception and as far as my experience in this hotel, is very unpleasant, she would not even say good morning nor smile, and look at you like if you were not paying the price for staying there... Perhaps she should join the Jockey's Club for a couple of nights....	
